reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars They definitely work.
reviews.reviewText: I had a TRT injection yesterday afternoon. Dr put a couple pieces of tape and some tagaderm which came loose at 4am. I grabbed these straps, cleaned the area and closed the wound back up.When I got to the ER, the Dr looked at it and said, "Its not bleeding. you did a great job. That's better than what we would've done here." He didn't even put gloves on. Just said good job several times and discharged me. That tells me two things. 1. These things work. And 2. I'm about to get a massive bill for walking through the ER and basically saying hi....

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great product and Great Results
reviews.reviewText: I read the reviews which overall seemed good except for maybe an adhesion issue. I am super active so I didn't want to chance it and added two bandaids to the outer edges. I checked it after a day and probably didn't need them. The butterfly bandage is still intact and the zip ties held great. I am able to re-apply Neo-sporin between the zip ties so as not to keep irritating the wound. I would highly recommend. In fact, I bought a few more to have on hand. Great product!!!
